{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}} {{Use Australian English|date=November 2016}} The '''Doctors Reform Society of Australia''' (DRS), set up in 1973, is a medico-political [[thinktank]] and a medical association of [[medical practitioner]]s and [[medical student]]s that has advocated a range of alternative views to those of the [[Australian Medical Association]].
Their initial focus was on [[universal health care]] or [[health insurance]] leading up to the establishment of the then "Medibank", now [[Medicare Australia]]. The DRS publishes the [https://web.archive.org/web/20080626191528/http://www.drs.org.au/newdoc.htm New Doctor] journal.
