[[image:schmoeckpfuhlgraben.jpg|thumb|the Schmöckpfuhlgraben separates Heinersdorf and Blankenburg]]

The '''Schmöckpfuhl''' is a ditch in [[Berlin-Heinersdorf|Heinersdorf]] in the [[Pankow]] district of [[Berlin]].

It meanders above ground and partly subterraneously through allotment gardens and settlements and flows finally into the [[Panke]]. It is probably fed of wastewater from the allotment gardens.

